PACKAGE_MANAGEMENT_RULES:
üö® PACKAGE MANAGEMENT RULES (CRITICAL - BROWSER-BASED ENVIRONMENT) üö®

This is a BROWSER-BASED system. Users CANNOT run "npm install".
Any external package you import WILL CAUSE RUNTIME ERRORS.

‚ùå ABSOLUTELY BANNED PACKAGES (Will cause ReferenceError):
1. **prop-types** - Deprecated, legacy React pattern
   ‚ùå import PropTypes from "prop-types";
   ‚ùå Component.propTypes = { ... };

2. **class-validator** - Backend validation library
3. **joi** - Backend validation library
4. **yup** - Form validation (not available in browser)
5. **zod** - Schema validation (requires build step)
6. **axios** - Use fetch API instead
7. **lodash** - Use native JavaScript methods
8. **moment** - Use native Date or date-fns (if pre-bundled)
9. **uuid** - Use crypto.randomUUID() or Date.now()
10. **dotenv** - Environment variables (backend only)
11. **express** - Backend server framework
12. **mongoose** - Database ORM (backend only)
13. **any @types/* packages** - TypeScript types (not needed in JSX)

‚ùå NEVER IMPORT THESE PATTERNS:
- import Something from "package-name";  (unless it's in SUPPORTED list)
- require("package-name");
- Any package that needs "npm install"

‚úÖ SUPPORTED (Pre-bundled in browser):
1. **react** - Core React library
   ‚úÖ import React from "react";
   ‚úÖ import { useState, useEffect, useMemo } from "react";

2. **react-dom** - React DOM rendering
   ‚úÖ import ReactDOM from "react-dom/client";

3. **Built-in Browser APIs** (NO import needed):
   ‚úÖ fetch() - HTTP requests
   ‚úÖ localStorage / sessionStorage
   ‚úÖ Date, Math, Array, Object (native JavaScript)
   ‚úÖ crypto.randomUUID() - Generate unique IDs
   ‚úÖ setTimeout, setInterval
   ‚úÖ URL, URLSearchParams
   ‚úÖ FormData, Blob, File

‚úÖ ALTERNATIVES TO BANNED PACKAGES:

**Instead of PropTypes:**
// ‚ùå DON'T USE
